  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Start with the salsa. Very finely chop the red onion. Scrape half\ninto a small bowl. Peel and dice the pineapple and add to the bowl\nof onion. Roughly chop half the coriander (stalks and all) and add\nthis too. Zest and squeeze in the juice of 1 lime, season and set the\nsalsa aside."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Next, stir the hot sauce into the yoghurt and season. Very finely\nshred the cabbage and scrape into a new bowl. Squeeze over the\njuice of the other lime, season then scrunch together with your\nhands – this will help it soften slightly."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Get a large frying pan over a high heat. Pour in the olive oil, then\ntip in the turkey mince. Use the back of your spoon to break the\nmince into smaller pieces, season, then add the remaining chopped\nred onion. Fry, stirring occasionally, until the mince is cooked\nthrough and browned, then stir through the fajita seasoning."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Meanwhile, heat the rice until piping hot, roughly chop the\nremaining coriander and mix together. Slice the avocados."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Assembly time. Heat the tortillas, then add to the centre of each\nthe spiced turkey, coriander rice, red cabbage, pineapple salsa, avo,\nhot sauce yoghurt and pickled jalapeños, if using. Fold over the\nends and roll up to seal. Cut in half and enjoy."
    }
  ],
